<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roman Criticizes Method of Cabinet Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803143894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0803143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a statement to our reporters today, Democratic 
Party [PD] Chairman Petre Roman referred to the recent 
government reshuffle, expressing his disappointment that it had 
been done without first consulting with the other political 
forces and, especially, without first consulting with 
parliament. The reshuffle was done in this way despite the fact 
that lately the government party and the other parliamentary 
parties had been engaged in a dialogue, Roman said. Such 
consultations would have been necessary, he assessed, as some of 
the offices subjected to the reshuffle are important for our 
national interests. 
  Regarding the talks conducted by PD representatives with the 
leaders of PDSR [Social Democracy Party of Romania], Roman said 
that actually they were discussions rather than negotiations 
merely intended to clear up certain things. However, 
consultations and the dialogue have to be continued in order to 
concretely solve the problems and sorrows of the people. 
  The PD leader said that the current government seems to be 
detached from reality, which is a serious matter, considering 
the way the people's problems and sorrows have accumulated. 
Those who bear high responsibility in our society ought to show 
interest for all such problems, Roman pointed out, saying that 
the time is ripe for a program of hope and confidence. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

