<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Solidarity Strikes Continue in Silesia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903111394 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0800 
GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Announcer] A strike organized by Solidarity 
started an hour ago in 100 enterprises in Katowice province. 
  [Correspondent Pagiela] The Wanda textile plant in 
Sosnowiec, the mining electronic equipment plant in Tychy, and 
the Fablok locomotive factory in Chrzanow are among the 
enterprises on strike. We have been told that the OPZZ 
[All-Polish Trade Union Agreement] unions have joined the 
strike. Despite earlier announcements, muncipal transport is 
not on strike in Silesia. Marek Kepski, chairman of the 
Solidarity Silesia-Dabrowa region, said that a strike of public 
transport would inconvenience the public, and Solidarity wants 
to avoid this. The decision as to whether a public transport 
strike should take place in Silesia will probably be made on 15 
March. 
  [Announcer] Piotr Pagiela was speaking from Katowice. 
  Public transport in Koszalin was not working between 0400 
and 
0700 hours because the work force of the MZK [Municipal 
Transport Enterprise] joined the Solidarity strike. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

