<H3> <TI>   UN Reports Cease-Fire Violations in Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803162694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0803162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Several cases of cease-fire violations were 
registered in Sarajevo yesterday, UN Protection Forces 
[UNPROFOR] representative Major Jose (La Bandeira) said today. 
Three soldiers of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army were injured by 
small arms fire from the Serbian aggressor's positions. 
  Major (La Bandeira) confirmed that six howitzers of the 
Serbian aggressor are positioned 900 meters inside the protected 
zone around Sarajevo. They are situated near Ilijas. UNPROFOR 
is negotiating their withdrawal with Karadzic's Serbs even 
though these howitzers should have long since been removed or 
placed under the control of the peace troops on the basis of the 
NATO ultimatum and the agreement reached at Sarajevo airport. 

