<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Reportedly Blaming Muslims for Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803224594 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2209 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0803224594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Dejan Lukic] </F>
  [Text] Washington, March 8 (TANJUG) -- United Nations 
experts have established that Moslems were responsible for the 
explosion at a Sarajevo market in early February, TANJUG learned 
from usually well-informed American circles. 
  The sources said that two officers of the U.N. commission, 
one from Great Britain and one from Belgium, independently came 
to the conclusion that the shell had been fired from the Moslem 
side. 
  The ballistics experts sent the report to the U.N. 
Protection 
Force (UNPROFOR), but the document apparently got side-tracked 
somewhere along the way, the sources said. The sources told 
TANJUG that the White House also had a copy of this report. 
  The French television network TF-1 recently broadcast a 
report by its New York correspondent which mentioned the 
UNPROFOR report blaming the Moslems for the massacre. The 
official UNPROFOR report on the massacre, which killed 68 
civilians and wounded around 200 according to Moslem media, said 
that it was not possible to establish the guilty party. 
  THE WASHINGTON POST said on Tuesday that the shell which 
caused the massacre at the Sarajevo market, judging from its 
effects, could have come from the Moslem side. This article is 
the first of its kind in a major U.S. newspaper which even 
allows for the possibility that Bosnian Serbs were not 
responsible for the massacre. 
  The massacre triggered NATO to issue an ultimatum and demand 
that Bosnian Serbs and Moslems withdraw or place under UNPROFOR 
control their heavy weapons in and around Sarajevo or face air 
strikes. Western politicians and media, however, interpreted 
this as an ultimatum and threat to Serbs, urging only them to 
honour the NATO ultimatum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

