<H3> <TI>   Details on Military Education Provided </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903091994 Prague DENNI TELEGRAF in Czech 3 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0903091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague DENNI TELEGRAF </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "kch"-signed: "Speculations Damaged the </F>
Military Academy"] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Vladimir Vetchy, chairman of 
the trade union organization at the Brno Military Academy, 
specified that experts of a productive age have been leaving the 
school, influenced by distorted information about its coming 
closure. An association was even organized to find immediate 
employment for them in the civilian sector under advantageous 
financial conditions. 
  The representatives of the Military Academy also denied 
reports yesterday about the students at the newly opened Air 
Force and Air Defense Faculty using Brno airport. The training 
of Brno pilots is to take place in Pardubice. 
  The Infantry Military School in Vyskov will specialize in 
the 
preparation of lower level commanders, and the third military 
academy in the Republic is the Military Medical School in Hradec 
Kralove. 

</TEXT>

