<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HZDS, SDL Leaders Continue Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803230394 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0803230394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Movement for a Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] has 
been holding talks with the Party of the Democratic Left [SDL] 
within the context of its coalition agreement with the Slovak 
National Party [SNS]. HZDS Deputy Chairman Sergej Kozlik said 
this after today's joint session of the HZDS and SNS 
parliamentary groups in Bratislava. At the same time, he said 
that they would not exclude an agreement with the SDL with 
regard to stabilizing the Cabinet for a certain limited period 
or until the elections, regardless of whom the HZDS was in 
coalition. 
  Answering a question regarding whether a cancellation of the 
coalition agreement with the SNS and concluding a new coalition 
with the SDL are being considered, Kozlik said that they had not 
looked at this issue from this point of view. 
  In this context, Miloslav Kona, chairman of the SNS 
parliamentary group, expressed the conviction that the SDL would 
change its stance on refusing a coalition with the SNS while its 
chairman is Jan Slota. 
  Commenting on the alleged offer of the presidential post to 
the SDL by Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar, Kozlik explained 
that, during a free debate outside the framework of the official 
HZDS-SDL talks, it had been noted that it would not be 
impossible for the HZDS to imagine an SDL candidate for the 
presidential post. However, this was not discussed as an actual 
offer. 
  The parliamentary groups of the coalition parties also 
discussed individual points of the agenda of the session of the 
National Council of the Slovak Republic, which will open on 9 
March. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

