<H3> <TI>   NATO Plane Hit Over Krajina; American Injured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803163394 Paris AFP in English 1628 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0803163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, March 8 (AFP) -- A NATO transport plane 
made an emergency landing in Croatia Tuesday [8 March] with an 
engine on fire, a North Atlantic Treaty Organisation spokesman 
said here. 
  An American, a Frenchman and a Briton aboard the 
twin-engined 
CASA 212 were injured, he said, but added that the crew had not 
reported being fired upon. However the Spanish defence ministry 
said the aircraft had been hit in the tail and the right engine. 
  Earlier reports from the United Nations Protection Force in 
Zagreb said that an unidentified Cessna had been fired upon over 
Croatia and forced to land. 

</TEXT>

