<H3> <TI>   Spanish Plane Hit; 3 Injured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803173194 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1700 GMT 
8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0803173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Spanish plane of the Aviocar type, which was on a 
mission controlling the airspace in Bosnia-Herzegovina, has been 
hit by antiaircraft fire. Three of its nine passengers, one 
British, one French, and one American, were slightly wounded by 
shrapnel. 
  The planes' crew of three pilots and a Spanish mechanic were 
not hurt, although it had to make an emergency landing at the 
Rijeka airport in Croatia. 
  The plane was transporting personnel between Split and 
Zagreb, in Croatian territory. It was flying over Krajina where 
there is often fighting between Serbs and Croats. So far, the 
origin of the antiaircraft fire has not been determined. 

</TEXT>

