<H3> <TI>   Serb `Terrorists' Fired on Plane </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803182894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0803182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The political department of the Croatian Ministry of 
Defense has issued the following statement: 
  Shortly after 1200 today a Spanish UN Protection Force plane 
took off from Zagreb for Split. When it was above the Plasko 
area, which is under the control of Serb terrorists, two 
missiles were fired at it. One missed the target and the other 
exploded near the plane and damaged its tail. 
  It can be reliably said that the missiles were fired by Serb 
terrorists, members of the so-called 39th Banija Corps. 
  There were four crew members and five passengers on the 
plane. Three of them were slightly wounded. The missiles were 
fired at 1235. 
  The plane made an emergency landing at Krk airport at 1252, 
the statement says. 

</TEXT>

