<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coalition Wants Rosati as Deputy Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803222594 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
2100 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0803222594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A meeting between representatives of the Democratic 
Left Alliance [SLD] and the Polish Peasant Party [PSL] has just 
ended at the Parkowa hostel in Warsaw. 
  [Reporter] A meeting of the SLD-PSL coalition is over. 
According to Jerzy Szmajdzinski, the coalition members 
acquainted themselves with the sociopolitical situation in 
Poland in the context of the spreading strike action by 
Solidarity. The government's readiness for talks with 
Solidarity has been reiterated. The SLD presented to Prime 
Minister Waldemar Pawlak a proposal that the deputy prime 
minister and finance minister portfolios be given to Dariusz 
Rosati. 
  As Szmajdzinski put it, the prime minister received the 
proposal in silence. It was agreed that, before the end of this 
week, Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak will hold a longer 
conversation with the candidate for deputy prime ministership. 
During this conversation, Pawlak will agree on conditions for 
cooperation with the new finance minister. 
  Journalists asked if the coalition members also discussed 
clauses in the Budget Law that oblige the Ministry of National 
Defense to purchase equipment only from Polish arms 
manufacturers. Answering this question, Jerzy Szmajdzinski 
stated that the SLD expects Minister Piotr Kolodziejczyk to 
indicate all of his reservations concerning the budget of his 
ministry during the Senate debate on the budget. 
  During the evening meeting, the coalition members also 
discussed sending the concordat to the Sejm. 

</TEXT>

