<H3> <TI>   Fidesz's Orban Launches Election Campaign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0703082194 Budapest MTI in English 2026 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0703082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 6 March (MTI) -- "The Federation of Young 
Democrats (Fidesz) is a party of balance and unity, which 
provides a political home for people with different world 
outlooks and ways of thinking," Fidesz Chairman Viktor Orban 
said in Szekesfehervar today. 
  Addressing the first rally of the Young Democrats' election 
campaign, Orban said, "Over the past few years the Fidesz proved 
that it could represent the ideas of political and national 
unity in an authentic way." 
  "The Fidesz was perhaps the first party in the 20th-century 
history of Hungarian liberalism which could reconcile liberalism 
with national commitment," he said. 
  The Fidesz chairman said the country needs a government 
which 
helps stabilize democarcy and is committed to Hungary's soonest 
possible membership in the European Union and NATO. "A liberal 
government has the best chance to cope with the tasks the 
country will face in the coming years," Orban said. 
  Concerning the strengthening of the Socialist Party, Orban 
said most people wish calm, security and a better life rather 
than a return to the past. 

</TEXT>

