<H3> <TI>   Solidarity Issues Communique on Strike Actions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803181394 Warsaw PAP in English 1655 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0803181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Gdansk, March 8--Eighty steel mills on Tuesday took 
part in the Solidarity-organised protest action, according to a 
communique issued by the Solidarity union national protest 
action headquarters. The communique, signed by Piotr Zak, says 
that Solidarity on Tuesday organised a two-hour warning in 69 
steel and iron enterprises, and raised money for the strike fund 
in eleven enterprises. 
  On Wednesday, two-hour warning strikes are to be held in the 
Silesia-Dabrowa and Lodz regions. Five more enterprises in the 
Koszalin region will follow suit of four enterprises in the 
province which staged strikes on Tuesday. 
  Solidarity railwaymen will stage strikes on March 11. 
Freight and passenger traffic will be stopped between 9 am and 
19 pm on Friday. The communique claims that the union has not 
received from the government "any proposal of negotiations." 

</TEXT>

