<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Resolution on Rebuilding Defense Industry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0703192294 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1722 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0703192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 7/3/1994 -- A communique issued 
in Bucharest on 7 March informs that, in compliance with the 
recommendation of the Supreme Council of Defense, the Romanian 
Government has adopted a resolution for the appointment, 
organization and functioning of a government board for the 
restructuring of the defense industry. 
  The restructuring of the defense industry is part of the 
reform programme developed by the Government of Romania, and its 
purpose is to adjust production capacities to the technical 
endowment requirements of the forces forming the national 
defense system, as well as to modernize and update certain 
units, to keep under conservation strictly specialized 
equipment, to convert, partly or entirely, some manufacturing 
units, to offer the personnel to be laid-off professional 
readjustment opportunities. 
  The main aim of the government board for the restructuring 
of 
the defense industry is to adapt the defense industry to the new 
demands of the market economy without affecting Romania's 
defense capabilities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

