<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Approval for European Integration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803214294 Prague CTK in English 1807 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0803214294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 8 (CTK) -- Sixty-nine percent of 
Slovaks consider Slovakia's integration into Europe successful 
and rate its military cooperation positively, according to the 
results of a January poll conducted by the Slovak Statistical 
Office. 
  Fifty-six percent of respondents, on the other hand, think 
Slovakia's economic performance internationally has been 
unsuccessful. 
  The activity of Slovak embassies abroad is judged as a 
disappointment by 42 percent. Twenty-nine percent think there 
are still too few embassies and consulates abroad, while 12 
percent reckon there are too many. 
  Slovaks are most satisfied with the performance of Slovak 
sportsmen abroad and the representation of Slovak culture, with 
two-thirds rating it positively. 

</TEXT>

