Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 March 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ethnic Albanians `Ignoring' Calls To Join Army </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0403163194 Tirana ATA in English 1111 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0403163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 3 (ATA) -- The Serbian authorities 
are presently calling up Albanian young men of the Istog commune 
born during the 1967-1977 period to serve in the Serbian Army. 
The young Albanians are ignoring the induction notices because 
they don't want to serve in the army "of a neighbouring 
totalitarian state" as they consider Serbia. The aim of these 
call-ups is to apply pressure on the Albanian young men to force 
them to abandon Kosova. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

