<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Policemen in Albanian Killing Allegedly Drunk </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803174594 Tirana ATA in English 1304 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0803174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 8 (ATA) -- Two drunk Serbian 
policemen killed Faik Adem Maloku and wounded Xhevat Bajzaku on 
March 6 in the "Lokomotiva" Cafe on the main road of 
Fushe-Kosova, during the control they made among the people in 
the cafe. 
  Maloku did not had his identity card with him and was 
explaining the police that he was a local inhabitant known by 
the people there, but one of the Serbian policeman shot Maloku 
dead with his pistol. 
  The other Albanian, Xhevat Bajzaku, tried to avoid the same 
tragedy on him, but he got seriously wounded by the drunk 
policemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

