<H3> <TI>   Official Denies Refugee Agreement With Germany </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903213194 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
2000 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0903213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The authorities of North Rhine-Westphalia 
postponed the deportation of several hundred refugees from 
Serbia and Montenegro via Romania, an action that should have 
started tomorrow, the Interior Ministry of that land, quoted by 
AFP, announced. [passage omitted] 
  The Romanian General Directorate for Passports within the 
Ministry of Interior told our reporters tonight that there is no 
understanding regarding the arrival in transit of refugees from 
Serbia and Montenegro. 
  Tonight, at 2100, our correspondent received information 
from 
the Romanian Embassy in Belgrade that the Romanian charge 
d'affaires, Constantin Garbea, was received today at the FRG 
Foreign Ministry upon his request, where he presented the 
official position of Romania in connection with the deportation 
of the Yugoslav refugees from Germany and their transit through 
Romania on their way to Yugoslavia. 
  It was noted that no understanding or accord between the 
Governments of Romania and Germany regarding the transit through 
Timisoara of Yugoslav citizens who will be deported from Germany 
has been reached and rumors that were circulating are groundless. 

</TEXT>

