<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet: Speech `Outrageous Attack' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903211794 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Cabinet of the Slovak Republic has held an 
extraordinary session to discuss the president's address at the 
National Council. The Cabinet adopted a statement expressing 
its great alarm and distress regarding the president's speech, 
which it considers to be an outrageous attack on the fundamental 
institutions of our young state that have been formed on the 
basis of democratic elections; the attack damages the name and 
status of the Slovak Republic abroad and significantly 
destabilizes the internal political situation, which is already 
rather complex. 
  The Cabinet on principle rejects the president's speech as 
confrontational and unprecedented, contradicting European 
political standards and human ethics and going beyond the 
constitutional powers of the president of the Republic, even 
more so because this Cabinet deserves credit for the formation 
of the independent and sovereign Slovak Republic and bears main 
responsibility for its development. 
  The Cabinet will submit the speech by the president of the 
Republic to a thorough analysis and will inform the citizens 
about its outcome. 

</TEXT>

