<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Proposes No-Confidence Vote in Meciar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903183794 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] Shortly before 1800 hours, Deputy 
Ladislav Pittner [Christian Democratic Movement] submitted the 
following proposal in parliament: 
  [Begin Pittner recording] I am submitting a proposal for a 
vote of no confidence in Vladimir Meciar, the prime minister of 
the Slovak Republic. 
  Vladimir Meciar, as prime minister of the Slovak Republic, 
has led the Slovak Republic into a political and economic 
crisis. By his statements, attitudes, and decisions, he has 
diminished the credibility of the Slovak Republic abroad; by the 
methods of his political work, on a long-term basis, he was 
unable to win over sufficient support within the minority 
government and in the Slovak Republic National Council. He was 
incapable of maintaining acceptable relations with the other 
supreme bodies of the state, in particular with the Slovak 
Republic National Council and president. 
  It is for this reason that, in harmony with the Slovak 
Republic Constitution, I submit this proposal, together with the 
list of signatures of the necessary number of deputies, to the 
Slovak Republic National Council, asking for this proposal to be 
discussed. [end recording] 
  [Announcer] The parliament will vote on Ladislav Pittner's 
proposal in a short while. 

</TEXT>

