<H3> <TI>   SNS Offers To Withdraw From Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903231094 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903231094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Slovak National Party [SNS] Chairman Jan Slota told 
a TASR correspondent that his party had suggested to the Party 
of the Democratic Left [SDL] chairman that it would withdraw 
from the coalition with the HZDS [Movement for a Democratic 
Slovakia] if it was inevitable in order to form an HZDS-SDL 
coalition before early parliamentary elections. He said that 
the SNS was aware that the problem that has arisen was not a 
result of politicking but of the economic collapse of this young 
republic. 
  SDL Chairman Peter Weiss reacted to Slota's offer to 
withdraw 
from the coalition with the following words: We are willing to 
negotiate with anyone, but today, after the president's speech, 
the situation is different from what it was yesterday. 
  Asked whether the SDL was united, Weiss responded that four 
deputies had not signed the proposal to dismiss the prime 
minister because they insisted that the issue of early elections 
should be resolved first. He added that the current crisis in 
the country could not be resolved by passing a vote of no 
confidence in Vladimir Meciar without agreeing on a date for 
early elections. 

</TEXT>

