<H3> <TI>   Soldiers' Association Opposes Ministry Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903134994 Bratislava REPUBLIKA in Slovak 7 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0903134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava REPUBLIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "A False Claim, To Say the Least"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava -- At its meeting in Zilina on Saturday 
[5 March], the Association of Slovak Soldiers (ASV) Presidium 
discussed the reasons cited by Defense Minister Imrich Andrejcak 
when he expressed his disagreement with the signing of an 
agreement on cooperation between the ASV and the Defense 
Ministry. It considers his claim about the Association's almost 
illegal conduct to be, to say the least, false. This statement 
is contained in a letter handed to TA SR by ASV Chairman 
Lieutenant-Colonel Milan Stegena. 
  According to the letter, the ASV Presidium has weighed the 
reasons and circumstances associated with them for the planned 
nationwide commemoration of the 55th anniversary of the 
repulsion of Hungarian aggression in March 1939 and, after 
taking all of them into consideration, especially the 
organizational requirements, has decided to hold the event on 26 
March. 

</TEXT>

