<H3> <TI>   RSK Informs Embassies of Croatian Offensive </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903211194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2003 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 9 Mar (TANJUG) -- The foreign ministry of 
the republic of Serb Krajina [RSK] today informed all diplomatic 
and consular missions in Belgrade about the major Croatian 
offensive in the area of the village of Kozjan near Korenica and 
Mali Alan on Mt. Velebit, near Gracac, ISKRA reports. 
  Following minor provocations on 4 March, the Croatian Army 
intensified its activities and is bringing in reinforcements 
with strong artillery backing, the information says. 
  The representatives of diplomatic and consular missions in 
Belgrade have been requested to inform their governments about 
these assaults by Croatia against the sovereignty of the RSK, 
and to raise the issue in international forums, in view of the 
fact that Croatia is violating all the cease-fire agreements 
signed with the RSK so far. 
  The Krajina Foreign Ministry warns that the latest attack 
against the RSK, if the Croatian offensive is not checked, could 
have dire consequences and could result in the escalation of the 
war in the region of former Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

