<H3> <TI>   Army Continues Attacks in Kozjan Region </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903155094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1343 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 9 Mar (TANJUG) -- There has been no letup in 
attacks by the Croatian Army in the region of Kozjan, east of 
Korenica, for four days, ISKRA [Croatian Serb news agency] has 
reported. Fierce fighting took place yesterday and the 
aggressor used mortars, multiple rocket launchers, and infantry 
weapons, ISKRA says, quoting the information office of the Serb 
army of Krajina general staff. Serb defenders have been 
returning the attacks and are successfully holding the defense 
lines, the statement says. 
  There was no peace in northern Dalmatia yesterday either. 
The Croatian Army opened fire from infantry weapons throughout 
the Drnis area, on the free territory of Kasic, and on villages 
in the Novigrad hinterland, and in the direction of Benkovac. 
There were no casualties in the attacks and the Serb defenders 
responded to all enemy attacks, ISKRA says. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

