<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Offensive in Doboj Continues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003125194 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1206 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1003125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Doboj, Mar 10 (TANJUG) - Moslem formations continued 
on Thursday their offensive on Serb settlements and positions in 
the broader area of the Serb-controlled town of Doboj, in 
northern Bosnia. 
  The strongest Moslem attacks with artillery support are 
taking place on Mount Ozren and Mount Trebava, south and east of 
Doboj. 
  Bosnian Serb military sources said that Moslem troops from 
Zavidovici are trying to make a breakthrough in the area on 
Mount Ozren in a bid to link up with Moslem forces from Maglaj. 
  The same source said that Serb fighters stopped the 
attackers 
with effective fire and forced them to retreat. 
  The Bosnian Serb Army command said that Moslem Leader Alija 
Izetbegovic had ordered all his units to take Doboj and Mount 
Trebava at any cost and that fresh units from central Bosnia 
have been brought into the Zavidovici area for this purpose 
since Moslem-Croat fighting there had abated in intensity. 
  Moslem units launched several attacks on Serb positions 
north 
of Maglaj, in northern Bosnia, Bosnian Serb military sources 
said. 
  The Herzegovina corps of the Bosnian Serb Army said on 
Thursday that Moslem formations on several ocassions opened 
infantry fire on Serb positions between Mostar and Nevesinje, in 
southwestern Bosnia, on Wednesday afternoon. 
  After the fire was responded to, the provocations ceased, it 
was said. A complete lull reigned on this part of the front 
during the past several months. 

</TEXT>

