<H3> <TI>   Production Fell 19 Percent in Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803175294 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0803175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Economic Info"] </F>
  [Text] According to the State Statistics Institute, the 
January industrial production in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], as compared with last year's 
monthly production figures, has decreased in average by 19 
percent. The production of manufacturing machinery is marking 
the biggest fall of 37.5 percent, followed by the production of 
reproduction materials (8 percent) and the consumer goods (2.4 
percent). 
  The January prices of the industrial products have gone up 
by 
13.1 percent, the market prices by 22 percent and the living 
costs by 18.8 percent. 

</TEXT>

