<H3> <TI>   Sejm Rejects Discussion of Zhirinovskiy Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003103394 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0835 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1003103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 10 Mar--The Sejm, which is deliberating 
today, has rejected a motion by the KPN [Confederation for an 
Independent Poland] parliamentary group for adding to the agenda 
a report by the foreign minister on actions taken by the 
government to prevent any public insults of the Polish Republic 
and its bodies by foreigners. 
  Justifying the motion, the KPN recalled that Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy is to come to Poland soon and asked whether the 
government had taken any actions to stop the visit. The motion 
was supported by 118 deputies; 133 voted against and 69 
abstained. 
  Next, the Sejm approved a motion by Deputy Bogdan Pek to 
discuss the government's report on the privatization of Bank 
Slaski as the first item on the agenda. 

</TEXT>

