<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee Protests Seizure of Kosovar Institute </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003175694 Tirana Radio Tirana Network in Albanian 1430 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1003175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana Radio Tirana Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Albanian Helsinki Committee has addressed a 
protest to the Serbian Government, energetically reacting 
against the violent act of usurping the Albanological Institute 
in Prishtina. The protest states that this Serbian apartheid and 
segregation against the ethnic Albanians in former Yugoslavia is 
every day exterminating every kind of institution and legal 
structure of the spiritual and material world in Kosova. This 
is a manifestation of another form of ethnic cleansing, which 
the Belgrade authorities are practicing in Kosova. 
  The Albanian Helsinki Committee addresses all international 
institutions to stop, as soon as possible, these inhuman acts 
that incite and provoke the spread of war toward the south of 
Balkans at any cost. The committee feels that the European 
consciousness cannot stand indifferent when academies are closed 
in front of its eyes, cultural and academic institutions are 
locked, and art and culture representatives are beaten, 
maltreated, and imprisoned, thus challenging the European 
science and culture itself. 
  The Albanian Helsinki Committee expresses its conviction 
that 
the international public, as well as the recent approved 
resolutions accepting the CSCE Commission as observers against 
the violations of human rights of Albanians in former 
Yugoslavia, will exert their pressure to stop Serbian 
repression, apartheid, and segregation in Kosova. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

