<H3> <TI>   Greece's Papoulias Arrives in Belgrade for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103124194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1212 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Belgrade, 11 Mar (TANJUG)--At noon today, Greek 
Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias arrived in Belgrade, where he 
is to have talks with Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic. He 
was welcomed at Belgrade aiport by Federal Deputy Prime Minister 
Zeljko Simic. 
  Milosevic and Papoulias are expected to exchange views on 
the 
problems of the peace process on former Yugoslavia, particularly 
on the crisis in former Bosnia-Herzegovina after the signing of 
the Washington plan for the creation of the Muslim-Croat 
federation and a confederation with the Republic of Croatia. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

