<H3> <TI>   Kontic To Request Extension of UN Mandate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003161094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1424 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1003161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Belgrade, 10 Mar (TANJUG)--At its session today 
presided over by Yugoslav Prime Minister Radoje Kontic the 
federal government examined a report on spring sowing and 
adopted a decision on protected prices of basic agricultural 
products, the Federal Ministry of Information announced in a 
statement. [passage omitted] 
  The government also examined and endorsed a letter which the 
federal prime minister is to send to UN Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali regarding the extension of the UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces] mandate in the protected zones on the 
territory of the former Yugoslavia. It has been concluded that 
the presence of the UN peace forces in the protected zones is an 
important factor for the creation of the necessary conditions 
for reaching a political solution to the problem. 
  The government was also informed about actions taken by the 
Federal Ministry of Foreign Affairs in connection with a 
decision of the German authorities to expel FRY [Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia] citizens whose status in Germany has not 
been legalized. The Ministry of Foreign Affairs has been tasked 
with continuing and intensifying contacts with the relevant 
German authorities so that the full protection of the rights and 
interests of all FRY citizens in Germany may be secured, with 
particular insistence on the full application of the current 
international conventions and practice, the statement says. 
[passage omitted] 
  Milenko Perovic, hitherto the Montenegrin president's 
secretary general, has been appointed chairman of the Federal 
Council of Magistrates. 
  New Deputy Prime Minister Uros Klikovac has been appointed 
chairman of the Federal Commission for the Political and Legal 
System, the Federal Ministry of Information statement concludes. 

</TEXT>

