<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Resolutions Condemning Serb Violence Praised </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003214194 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1003214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The 50th Session of the UN Human Rights Commission 
held in Geneva has approved two resolutions on Kosova, initiated 
by the United States and Pakistan. These resolutions condemn the 
brutality, acts, and violence of the Serbian regime against the 
Albanians of Kosova. 
  Welcoming the approval of these two resolutions, the 
government of the republic of Kosova has issued a public 
communique stressing that Belgrade has been shown to be 
responsible for violating the basic freedoms and rights of the 
Albanian people. Thus, the UN resolutions express the will of 
the civilized peoples in the world to object to every violation 
of human rights in Kosova and undertake actions in this regard. 
  The government of the republic of Kosova is of the opinion 
that the will expressed by its people is the only basis for a 
final solution. The communique asks the UN to increase its 
efforts to be present in Kosova to help prevent conflict and 
guarantee the return of democratic institutions to normality. 

</TEXT>

