<H3> <TI>   Generals Brief U.S. Envoy on Army-HVO Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003165894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1003165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Press Center of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 
reports that Army General Rasim Delic and Brigadier-General 
Jovan Divjak held talks with General John Galvin, special 
military envoy of U.S. President Clinton, in Sarajevo today. 
  The discussion concerned further steps in the implementation 
of the agreement between the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army and the 
Croatian Defense Council [HVO], which will be taken in the 
coming days. During the talks, General Delic informed General 
Galvin of the possible principles of a military solution in the 
future Bosnia-Herzegovina federation, which separately outlines 
possible solutions for the transitional period. 
  At the end of today's talks General Galvin expressed 
optimism 
about the future course of the talks, absolutely acknowledging 
all the difficulties that are possible in the course of the 
realization of the agreement, especially in the transitional 
period. 
  The talks of the representatives of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Army and the HVO about a military solution in the future 
Bosnia-Herzegovina federation are scheduled to commence tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

