<F P=102>  AU1003201894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1003201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the Serbian Consultative 
Council, the Council of the Congress of Bosnian-Muslim 
Intellectuals, and the Croatian Coordinating Committee held a 
joint meeting today at which they examined the general agreement 
on the establishment of a federation and the general agreement 
on confederation with Croatia. 
  The joint stance of the Serbian Consultative Council, the 
Council of the Congress of the Bosnian-Muslim Intellectuals, and 
the Croatian Coordinating Committee, is that the sovereignty of 
Bosnia- Herzegovina as a state over its entire territory, peace, 
and human rights for all its citizens and peoples must be 
secured in the future documents, and this appears in a statement 
from today's meeting. 
  At the meeting they expressed their full support for the 
initiative to call an assembly of the citizens of Serbian 
nationality and Serbian ethnic origin, as was initiated by the 
Serbian Consultative Council, the statement reads. 

