<H3> <TI>   Krajina's Jarcevic Predicts `All-Out War' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003162394 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1003162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with RSK Foreign Minister Slobodan Jarcevic by </F>
news announcer in the Belgrade Radio studio on 10 March--live] 
  [Text] [Announcer] Mr. Jarcevic, could you briefly give us 
your comments on the latest attacks by Croatia? 
  [Jarcevic] Croatia is not attacking the Serbian positions in 
the republic of Serbian Krajina [RSK], but has carried out 
aggression on the territory of the Korenica commune. Supported 
with artillery and tanks, Croatian soldiers have stormed that 
territory. Moreover, in northwestern Dalmatia, they are 
attacking the communes of Obrovac and Benkovac. 
  In the eastern part of the republic of Serbian Krajina, 
around Vinkovci, they are also attacking us with artillery and 
infantry weapons. This is only a prelude, and I am expecting 
all-out war between the Republic of Croatia and the republic of 
Serbian Krajina. 
  [Announcer] On what do you base your views? 
  [Jarcevic] General Tudjman was given support in all the 
international bodies, in the United Nations, the CSCE, and the 
European Union. Washington is now firmly supporting him in his 
calls for the reintegration of the republic of Serbian Krajina 
into the Republic of Croatia. He knows that he cannot 
accomplish this with the agreement of the Serbian people who 
live in the republic of Serbian Krajina or those Serbs whom he 
has expelled from the Republic of Croatia. He is only left with 
war and it is certain that in the secret connections with 
Western countries he has been given the green light for that. 
  [Announcer] Thank you. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

