<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PD-FSN on Fairness of Moldovan Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003065494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1003065494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Party [PD-FSN] is following with 
concern recent developments in the political and socioeconomic 
activity in the Republic of Moldova, a communique received from 
the PD-FSN Executive Bureau emphasizes. As an observer at the 
recent elections in the Republic of Moldova, the PD-FSN believes 
that the opposition parties have been systematically hampered in 
addressing the electorate, while the ruling party, with the 
support of the presidency, benefited from unlimited access to 
the television station. 
  The communique points out that the organization, a week 
after 
the election and during the absence of observers, of the 
sociological poll entitled Consulting the People, is viewed as 
something futile and the possible transformation of the poll 
into a referendum on the basis of a presidential decree is 
inacceptable. 

</TEXT>

