<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Walesa on TV Council, Budget, Court Case </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0903134894 Warsaw RZECZPOSPOLITA in Polish 9 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> WS0903134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw RZECZPOSPOLITA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by M.U.: "Walesa: I Must Check the Budget"; last </F>
paragraph unattributed] 
  [Text] Asked whether he will sign the budget, President 
Walesa said that he must first check it. "If it corresponds to 
my hopes, and these hopes spring from the people, then I will 
sign it," he stated. 
  Lech Walesa declared his support for the head of the 
Ministry 
of National Defense, who announced that he will institute legal 
proceedings in the Constitutional Tribunal because the Sejm 
encroached upon the powers of the executive branch by ordering 
the Defense Ministry to purchase equipment made exclusively in 
Poland. "In new democracies, when new deputies come, they think 
that everything depends on them," he added. 
  Commenting on his conflict with the National Council of 
Radio 
and Television [KRRiT], the president said: "I expect several 
moves that will make the task easier for me." Asked what kinds 
of moves he meant, he said: "effective," and, on the part of 
KRRiT, moves "making action and life easier for the president." 
Asked about the possibility of Ryszard Bender's leaving the 
council, he said that he has a few friends in KRRiT. Concerning 
Andrzej Zaorski, who is said to be the presidential candidate 
for the council's chairman, the president said: "He is a good 
expert." As to the candidacy of Aleksander Kwasniewski to the 
post of president, he said: "He will definitely be defeated by 
me." 
  Lech Walesa may refuse to sign the Budget Law, just like any 
other law. It would then return to the Sejm, which may overturn 
the presidential veto with a two-thirds majority vote. The 
Sejm's arithmetic suggests that the Sejm should not have any 
problem doing just that, if necessary. The lack of the 
president's signature would also in no way affect implementation 
of the budget. 

</TEXT>

