<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Receives French Chief of Staff </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003205894 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1737 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1003205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 10 Mar--On 10 March, Prime Minister Waldemar 
Pawlak received Marshal Jacques Lanxade, chief of staff of the 
French Army. The government press office reported that Alain 
Bry, French ambassador to Poland, and General Tadeusz Wilecki, 
chief of the general staff of the Polish Army, were also present. 
  Poland and France signed an agreement on defense 
cooperation. 
Marshall Lanxade and Gen. Wilecki briefed the prime minister on 
the scope of the cooperation and stressed the importance of 
individual contacts between officers of both armies. 
  Polish and French soldiers will have an opportunity to meet 
in Normandy in June during the 50th anniversary of the D-day 
landings on the continent. The government press office 
communique says that the marshal assured the prime minister that 
France would support Poland's aspiration for full integration 
with the Western security system. 

</TEXT>

