<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement With London Club on Settling Debt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103111194 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
1000 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Poland has reached an agreement with the London 
Club, whose members are our commercial bank creditors. 
Difficult negotiations have been going on for four years, and 
finally last night there was a breakthrough. Agreement was 
reached on the main conditions for settling the Polish debt. 
  These conditions include a comprehensive and realistic 
reduction of the debt, according to the statement published this 
morning. Mr. Krzysztof Krowacki, who led our delegation, says 
the agreement fulfills the basic requirements of the Polish 
side. First of all, our payments will be within the framework 
of the projected capabilities of the balance of payments and the 
state budget. They will be low in the first five years and will 
remain low during the most intensive period of payments due in 
accordance with agreements with the Paris Club. All of the 
components of the debt have been reduced. Also reduced were the 
costs of servicing the debt. Repayment periods will be longer, 
payments per one unit of debt will be lower, and the debt itself 
will be reduced further. The combined reduction of the debt 
exceeds 45 percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

