<H3> <TI>   Czech Army Unit To Head for Bosnia Hot Spot </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903181094 Prague CTK in English 1516 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0903181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 9 (CTK) -- A Czech Army mechanized 
company will soon be transferred from Croatia to 
Bosnia-Herzegovina to reinforce UNPROFOR [United Nations 
Protection Force] troops in a trouble spot north of Sarajevo, 
Premier Vaclav Klaus announced today. 
  The Czech government approved the move based on a proposal 
by 
Defense Minister Antonin Baudys, who was responding to a request 
by UNPROFOR leaders. 

</TEXT>

