<H3> <TI>   Poland Offers To Send 150 Soldiers to Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003094094 Warsaw PAP in English 2330 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1003094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New York, March 9 -- PAP has learned from British 
sources that Poland has offered to send an additional 150 
soldiers to the former Yugoslavia. The decision was adopted in 
reply to an appeal of the UN secretary general calling for the 
strengthening of UNPROFOR [United Nations Protection Force] 
forces in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  PAP has also learned that Polish General Jozef Chmiel will 
soon assume command of the northern sector of UNPROFOR. 
  The Polish mission at the UN has not officially confirmed 
Poland's offer to send the additional soldiers. 

</TEXT>

