<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Slovakia Welcomes U.S. Initiative on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903203394 Prague CTK in English 1709 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0903203394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 9 (CTK) -- The Slovak Foreign 
Ministry welcomes the proposal to create a Bosnian-Croatian 
federation as a possible positive impulse for further 
developments in Bosnia-Herzegovina, a ministry statement handed 
to CTK on Wednesday [9 March] reads. 
  The statement praises the United States' contribution to 
attaining the agreement and also the significant role of Russia 
in the search for a peaceful solution to the crisis surrounding 
Sarajevo. 
  The ministry favors resolving the crisis in the former 
Yugoslavia by peaceful means. "We support all processes based on 
mutual consent, understanding and tolerance. We welcome every 
initiative which could lead to the ending of the war in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina," the statement reads. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-8551 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu049__a94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-049-A </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  14 March 1994 </DATE1>

