<H3> <TI>   Zhelev Visits Nuclear Research Center in Geneva </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903210094 Sofia BTA in English 1645 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0903210094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, March 9 (BTA) -- President Zhelyu Zhelev of 
Bulgaria today visited the European Organization for Nuclear 
Research (CERN) in Geneva. He arrived here from Paris on his 
way back to Bulgaria. Conferring with Prof. Llewellyn Smith, 
director general of CERN, Dr. Zhelev expressed the hope that 
cooperation between CERN and Bulgaria will help this country 
preserve its scientific potential in the transitional period, 
especially in the field of high-energy physics. President 
Zhelev confirmed Bulgaria's determination to gain full CERN 
membership which has already been granted to some Central 
European countries. 
  The Deputy Minister of Science and Education Prof. Boris 
Gulubov, who is accompanying the President, handed the CERN 
managers a draft update of the effective agreement on 
cooperation and expressed the readiness of the Bulgarian 
Government to continue the negotiations on the terms and the 
character of future relations. 
  The Bulgarian president was also accompanied by Bulgarian 
physicists of the Bulgarian Academy of Science and Sofia 
University. 

</TEXT>

