<H3> <TI>   Ministry Summons Yugoslav Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803174194 Tirana ATA in English 1112 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0803174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Foreign Ministry Works To Free Albanian Pair Arrested in </F>
Montenegro" -- ATA headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, March 8 (ATA) -- The Yugoslav charge 
d'affaires was called to the Foreign Ministry on March 3, for a 
discussion of the arrest in Montenegro of Socialist Party Deputy 
Moikom Zeqo and the chairman of the National Unity Party, Idajet 
Beqiri. The charge informed ministry officials that on February 
27th at about 2300 [2200 GMT] hours during a normal check of a 
car with Yugoslav plates in the village of Zelenovice of Ulqin 
district, police arrested Zeqo and Beqiri because they had no 
visas for Yugoslavia. They apparently had entered Yugoslavia 
illegally by crossing Lake of Shkoder by boat. 
  On March 4, the Albanian Government demanded that the 
Yugoslav authorities describe the conditions of the detainees 
and say what measures have been taken against them, but Yugoslav 
Embassy had no further information. The Albanians have lodged a 
protest demanding that visas be issued for three persons who are 
supposed to be in touch with the arrested men. At the same time 
the Albanian Embassy in Belgrade was informed, and the charge 
d'affaires was sent to Montenegro immediately. 
  Several demands have been sent to the Yugoslav Embassy in 
Tirana, but so far no news has been received about the arrested 
men and no visas have been issued to those who like to visit 
them. 

</TEXT>

