<H3> <TI>   Russia Offers Cooperation, Economic Assistance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903200394 Sofia BTA in English 1716 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0903200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, March 9 (BTA) -- Deputy Prime Minister 
Evgeni Matinchev today received a government delegation of the 
Russian Federation, led by Chairman of the State 
Machine-Building Committee Anatoliy Ogurtsov. The meeting was 
attended by Deputy Prime Minister Valentin Karabashev, Chairman 
of the Power Engineering Committee Nikita Shervashidze, and 
Deputy Minister of Industry Racho Petrov. The prospects of 
Bulgarian-Russian relations in industry were on the agenda. 
  Mr. Ogurtsov declared that Russian enterprises are now ready 
for wide-scale cooperation with Bulgaria and for all-round 
assistance. He stressed that this is the official stand of the 
Russian Government. The sides considered some specific aspects 
of cooperation in power and mechanical engineering, the debts 
which Bulgaria and Russia owe each other and some other problems. 
  Mr. Karabashev familiarized the guests with the Bulgarian 
Government's decision on reciprocal settlement of obligations 
and asked Mr. Ogurtsov to assist for a prompt reply from the 
Russian Government, containing its specific proposals on the 
matter, the Government said in a press release. 

</TEXT>

