<H3> <TI>   Fur Presses for Autonomy for National Minorities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003080194 Budapest MTI in English 2050 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1003080194 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 9 March (MTI) -- The ethnic Hungarian 
minorities living outside of Hungary would gain the best chance 
for survival by being granted autonomy, Hungarian Democratic 
Forum (MDF) Chairman Lajos Fur told a rally at Salgotarjan, 
northern Hungary, tonight. 
  "Hungary's internal stability and international relations, 
drawing a protective net around the country, are insufficient 
for the security of the country. Nor is it sufficient to keep 
the Army on a level enabling it to defend the country. For the 
security of Hungary, appropriate conditions should be guaranteed 
for the survival of ethnic Hungarian communities abroad," Fur 
said. 
  The rally was attended by members of the MDF National 
Presidium and the cabinet. 

</TEXT>

