Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 10--The presidium of the national 
board of the Liberal Democratic Congress (KLD) on Thursday 
voiced "its deep indignation at the position taken by the Polish 
Foreign Ministry on the resolution of the U.N. Human Rights 
Commission condemning the violation of human and civic rights in 
China." 
  During Wednesday's vote in Geneva on the Chinese motion to 
give up voting on the resolution demanding that human rights be 
observed in China, the polish delegate abstained. 
  "We demand a decisive change in the Foreign Ministry's stand 
on that issue as well as a policy that would prevent similarly 
discrediting actions from taking place in the future," a 
statement issued by the KLD said. 

