<H3> <TI>   Solidarity, Center Right Join Forces </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003183994 Warsaw PAP in English 1423 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1003183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rzeszow, March 10 -- The Solidarity Trade Union and 
six centre-right parties in Rzeszow have struck a regional 
election agreement to cooperate in the forthcoming local 
government elections, the leaders of the groupings said on 
Thursday, claiming that "this is an alliance against the 
Democratic Left Alliance (SLD)." 
  The regional Non-Party Reform Bloc (BBWR) is seeking to join 
the group but the coalition members, including the Christian 
National Union (ZCHN), the Confederation For an Independent 
Poland (KPN), the Peasant Agreement (PL), the Movement For the 
Republic of Poland (RDR), the Peasant Christian Party (SLCH) and 
the Centre Alliance (PC), have put off the decision till next 
week. The coalition's hesitance is caused by its "reservation 
towards one of the Rzeszow leaders of this political 
association." 
  The agreement signatories are discussing the name of the new 
bloc and its election manifesto. 

</TEXT>

