<H3> <TI>   Jaruzelski Prepared To Face State Tribunal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003103494 Warsaw PAP in English 1534 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1003103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 9 -- Wojciech Jaruzelski told a Sejm 
committee today that he was prepared to face the Tribunal of 
State if the Sejm decided he should do it. 
  "I will accept the Sejm's decision with full understanding 
and respect, and with the hope that the tribunal will be 
impartial, honest and just," said the general who introduced 
martial law in Poland on 13 December, 1981 after 16 months of a 
political showdown between the solidarity trade union and the 
communist authorities. 
  Today's session of the Sejm Committee for Constitutional 
Accountability was the first in a series of sessions during 
which Jaruzelski and other former politicians accused of 
implementing martial law will answer questions from MP's. 

</TEXT>

