<H3> <TI>   Expelled SLD Deputies Not To Join Opposition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903215794 Warsaw PAP in English 2131 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0903215794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 9 -- Democratic Left Alliance Deputy 
(SLD) Andrzej Lipski declared during a Wednesday meeting of the 
SLD parliamentary floor group that the group of deputies who 
lost membership in the SLD caucus after a Saturday vote against 
the 1994 budget, will not join the opposition and will continue 
to support the SLD programme. 
  Four SLD members: Piotr Ikonowicz, Andrzej Lipski, Cezary 
Mizejewski (Polish Socialist Party -- PPS) and Stanislaw 
Wisniewski (All-Poland alliance of Trade Unions -- OPZZ) were 
expelled from the caucus after they violated the caucus 
discipline in the budget vote. 
  "I want to stress clearly that we are not forming an 
opposition. we will create the PPS circle, but we will still be 
supporting these activities of the cabinet, which will aim at 
the implementation of the SLD programme," said Lipski. 

</TEXT>

