<F P=103> AU0903151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 9 (CTK) -- "I have known the 
president long enough and I would continue to respect him. 
However, I have mixed feelings about the personal attacks in 
his speech," the chairman of the Movement for a Democratic 
Slovakia (HZDS) deputies group, Tibor Cabaj, said today. 
  Deputy premier and honorary chairman of the coalition Slovak 
National Party (SNS) Jozef Prokes called the speech of President 
Michal Kovac confrontational, saying Kovac should first have 
consulted with the government, at least about those parts in 
which he spoke about the country's situation. "The government is 
responsible for running the country, not the president," he said. 

