<F P=102>  AU1003214894 Prague CTK in English 2121 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1003214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 10 (CTK) -- The opposition 
Democratic Left Party (SDL) will support the dismissal of 
Vladimir Meciar's cabinet only if it receives sufficient 
guarantee that early elections will be held, SDL Chairman Peter 
Weiss told CTK today. 
  The SDL fears that if Meciar's government is dismissed, some 
parties will lose interest in the elections, he added. 
  "If people underestimate the need for new elections, they do 
not understand the depth of political crisis in Slovakia," Weiss 
said. The position of the SDL is influenced by the fact that 
some unnamed politicians are ignoring the need for elections for 
which the SDL has been calling for a year, he said. 

</TEXT>

