<H3> <TI>   SDL Deputy Calls on Meciar To Resign, Debate To End </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1103131494 Prague CTK in English 0954 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1103131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava March 11 (CTK) -- In the renewed debate 
on confidence in the Slovak Government this morning, Deputy 
Chairman of the Democratic Left Party (SDL) Milan Ftacnik called 
on Premier Vladimir Meciar to resign or for the debate to be 
ended. 
  "The discussion is clearly only being prolonged, and 
deputies 
are straying from the matter in hand," Ftacnik said, calling on 
the premier to "pluck up courage" and make a speech. If he did 
not, then it was "clearly time to end the debate." 
  Chairman of Parliament Ivan Gasparovic said in reaction to 
this that the debate could be ended if deputies stopped asking 
for permission to speak. Ftacnik's appeal was not passed as a 
formal motion, and the debate continues with a speech by Culture 
Minister Dusan Slobodnik on the theme of success in the 
increasing of Slovakia's profile and the necessity of the 
Bojnicky Altar being returned from the Czech Republic. 
  After Ftacnik's speech, Meciar went to sit next to Deputy 
Chairman of Parliament and SDL chairman Peter Weiss and started 
talking to him. 

