<H3> <TI>   SDL's Kanis Confirms HZDS Offered Him Presidency </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1103134794 Prague CTK in English 1039 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1103134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bratislava, March 10 (CTK) -- Pavol Kanis, a 
parliamentary deputy for the SDL [Party of the Democratic Left], 
confirms in the daily NARODNA OBRODA today that Meciar has 
offered him the post of Slovak president during talks between 
representatives of the SDL and the Movement for a Democratic 
Slovakia (HZDS). 
  "During the talks important and unimportant things are said. 
I understood this offer as Meciar merely tossing out the 
possibility," Kanis says. 
  Asked why he did not put his signature under the proposal 
for 
a confidence vote in the government, which was signed by the 
majority of SDL deputies, Kanis says: "The SDL strategy places 
the decision on an early election date above other things, and I 
am bound to comply with the party strategy. I am expecting that 
others will also behave in harmony with the party's line," he 
adds. 
  Kanis says that the statement by Slovak National Party (SNS) 
Chairman Jan Slota that he could leave the government coalition 
to the benefit of the peace in the state could be described 
without exaggeration as "a statement by a real statesman." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

