<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministries To Close Albanian Radio, TV Stations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003065894 Tirana ATA in English 1115 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1003065894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Albanian Language Materials Censored in the FYROM" -- ATA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, March 9 (ATA) -- The Kosovar newspaper 
RILINDJA of March 8 reports that it expects some of the private 
radio and television stations broadcasting in Albanian in the 
former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia (FYROM) to be closed down 
on the initiative of several of the government ministries. 
  The RILINDJA commentary says that this action is indicative 
of the FYROM decision to eliminate the Albanian language from 
the mass media. 
  In keeping with this policy, the Macedonian police recently 
confiscated 200 copies of SHKENDIA magazine published in Kosova 
at the border point between Kosova and the FYROM, in the 
vicinity of Jazhice. The confiscation was explained by saying 
that the educational nature of the magazine made it subject to 
censorship. According to the chief of the customs house, this 
magazine "must be read" before its sale can be permitted. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

