<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klaus Speaks of Dismissal of Meciar Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103180994 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1700 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus spoke to Czech Radio 
about the dismissal of Slovak Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar: 
  It is in the interest of the Czech Republic that Slovakia is 
a stable, prospering state, and for this it needs a government 
that enjoys the trust of the Slovak public. The Czech 
Government also needs a partner. This is why we hope that the 
Slovak Government crisis is quickly over. I would like to thank 
Prime Minister Meciar and the outgoing Slovak Cabinet for their 
correct attitude with regard to Czech-Slovak relations and, 
above all, for our joint patient search for constructive 
solutions in the tense moments when our common state was 
splitting. 

</TEXT>

