<H3> <TI>   French, Czechs To Publish RESPEKT Jointly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1403085494 Prague MLADA FRONTA DNES in Czech 26 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1403085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague MLADA FRONTA DNES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "red": "The Weekly RESPEKT Will Have a New </F>
Publisher"] 
  [Text] Prague--In the very near future, the R-Presse 
company will become the new publisher of the prestigious weekly 
RESPEKT. The agreement on founding this company was signed 
yesterday in the morning by the representatives of the present 
publisher of RESPEKT (RPK Co.) and the Czech-French MaFra 
company, which publishes the daily MLADA FRONTA DNES. 
  RESPEKT emerged at the beginning 1990 as the successor to 
INFORMACNI SERVIS, which began publishing in November 1989. In 
1992, it was awarded the prize of American journalists--Magazine 
of the Year. Previous winners have included THE ECONOMIST, LE 
MONDE, and the FINANCIAL TIMES. 
  MaFra will hold a 51 percent stake in R-Presse, while the 
current publisher of RESPEKT will have 49 percent. 

</TEXT>

