<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak Says Strikers' Overall Demands Justified </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1203002694 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1800 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1203002694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In an interview for the "First Program" of Polish 
Radio and for the Polish Press Agency, Prime Minister Waldemar 
Pawlak said that the overall demands of Solidarity were 
justified but could not be achieved through strikes: 
  [Begin Pawlak recording] When we look at these demands, 
these general demands concerning, for example, an increase in 
real wages, I have to say that I, too, am in favor of the 
implementation of these demands. The [word indistinct] of 
putting forward such a demand is perhaps very big, and the 
general, noble, intention is very visible, but afterwards it has 
to be implemented. We want, through our actions, to bring about 
the implementation of this intention. When we speak of limiting 
the growth of energy carriers, I, too, am in favor of such a 
solution. In this budget, we can already see a visible decrease 
in the growth rate of energy prices in comparison with what had 
been planned as late as in the second half of last year or 
compared with the growth rate of prices that were implemented 
last year. 
  I would like to remind you that our government limited these 
price increases, and it seems to me that the difference between 
us here lies in how to implement these demands successfully. I 
am also in favor of implementing them. As I have said, however, 
if we were to discuss and compete on the level of ideas as to 
how to do this better and more quickly, it would certainly be of 
benefit to us all. I would encourage the holding of such a 
discussion and such a debate. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

