<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO Aircraft Halt Serbs Shelling Bihac </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1303115794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1303115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The morning of Bairam [Muslim holiday] in Bihac has 
started with heavy artillery attacks by chetniks from the nearby 
hills on all parts of the town, especially on Prekounje district 
and the industrial zone, as well as on the suburbs. Shells were 
fired from tanks, howitzers, and mortar-launchers. There is no 
peace on the front lines either. Since early this morning shell 
explosions and small-arms fire can be heard from this direction. 
  Fighters of the Bosnian Army's V Corps and members of the 
Internal Affairs Ministry and the Croat Defense Council are 
successfully repelling all attacks by aggressors who have been 
trying to break through our fighters' defense lines for over a 
month without success. 
  By the time of this report we have not received information 
on any casualties in this morning's attack. The shelling of the 
town and the suburbs stopped when NATO planes were seen flying 
above. The same happened during the night when NATO planes were 
swarming the skies above Bihac. 
  Muhamed Mulic reporting from Bihac for Bosnian Radio and TV. 

</TEXT>

