<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Muslim-Croat Land </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1303102794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0939 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1303102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kragujevac, 13 March (TANJUG)--The chairman of the 
Srpska republic assembly, Momcilo Krajisnik, said today that 
"the future Muslim-Croat federation can encompass 45 percent of 
the territory at the most because that is the amount of 
territory owned by Muslims and Croats." 
  Taking part in Kragujevac Radio's "Pecat Vremena" program, 
Krajisnik said that all other statements were means of exerting 
pressure to make the Serbs give up more territory. 
  However, Krajisnik said that other things apart from the 
percentage of the territory were also important. Quality is also 
important and the Serb side will insist on this. 
  Asked about the Serb position for the tripartite talks which 
will take place next week, Krajisnik said that many matters were 
already settled except for the territorial demarcation. 
  "Two entities exist on the territory of former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina now--the Muslim-Croat federation and the 
Srpska republic. We have also agreed to discuss other, 
previously settled, issues so it cannot be said that we do not 
want to cooperate," Krajisnik said. 

</TEXT>

