<H3> <TI>   HVO Violating Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1203223694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2100 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1203223694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Extremists of the Croatian Defense Council [HVO] 
have violated the cease-fire on the territory of the First Corps 
of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army. 
  A Bosnia-Herzegovina Army soldier has been killed by a 
sniper 
bullet while another was wounded. One member of the civilian 
police and one woman have also been wounded, which confirms that 
the enemy, following its murderous instincts, does not 
differentiate between civilians and soldiers [no date given]. 
  HVO fired two artillery rounds and seven 60-mm shells on 
positions held by units commanded by Avdija Rozajac in the 
region of Smailovici and Vasino Brdo on 11 March. Intensive 
sniper and small arms fire was opened along the entire defense 
line manned by this unit, particularly in the area of Zavrtaljka 
and Smailovici. Shortly after 1900 hours yesterday evening, HVO 
extremists carried out combat actions from M-84 machine guns, 
the so-called death- sowers, and anti-aircraft guns from the 
region of Brestovica, while they were noticed to be entrenching 
themselves intensively above the village of (?Gagve), which is a 
clear indication of their future intentions. 
  While UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] military observers 
were 
trying to mediate in the exchange of the body of one 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army soldier which the HVO has held for a 
long time, small arms fire was opened on the international 
military observers from HVO positions. UNPROFOR members 
assessed this as a serious indicent. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

