<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Unprecedented Horrors' Reported in Maglaj </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1203124394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1203124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Correspondent Hajrudin Sermic in Maglaj] Maglaj is 
going through the worst day of shelling since the beginning of 
the war. 
  The unprecedented horrors of Maglaj's inferno have descended 
on the population with a vengeance this morning. The heaviest 
shelling since the beginning of the war is going on as I am 
filing this report. Dozens of howitzer and mortar shells fired 
in salvos are crashing onto the town center every minute. The 
town is being shelled from several directions and by all means 
at the enemy's [Bosnian Serbs] disposal. Five Russian-made 
surface-to-surface missiles have been fired at civilians and the 
town itself this morning. Casualties have been reported, 
although the exact numbers are impossible to determine. 
  The Serb aggressor's offensive against the defense positions 
held by our [Muslim] defenders continues with the support of 
several hundred missiles fired from artillery pieces of all 
calibers. Concentrated fire is being directed at the area around 
the Nekolje dam. However, the fighters of the 201st Valiant 
Brigade and other units of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army cannot be 
swayed and are not giving in an inch. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

