<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Defeat `Futile' Muslim Attacks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403130094 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1218 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Doboj, March 14 (TANJUG)--Moslems launched five 
major infantry assaults with strong artillery support on the 
Doboj front in the north last night, but have been beaten back 
every time, Bosnian Serb military sources said on Monday. 
  Three of the attacks were on the Teslic front, south of 
Doboj, where the Moslems disregarded their festival of Bairam 
and engaged in strong offensive activities against the Serb 
positions. 
  Another abortive attack was launched on the south sector of 
the Trebava front, east of Doboj, which the Serbs beat back, 
suffering no casualties in the process. 
  Yet another futile effort to break through the Serb defence 
lines was undertaken on the western sector of the Ozren front, 
south of Doboj. Here, the Serbs also neutralised a Moslem 
terrorist group in an attempt to be infiltrated behind Bosnian 
Serb lines. 
  Serb villages on Mt. Ozren were subjected to strong 
small-arms fire by Moslem forces, which have been observed to be 
regrouping. 
  One Serb soldier was wounded by Croat small-arms fire from 
the direction of Orasje in the north after midnight, Serb 
military sources said. 
  Bosnian Serb positions were exposed to provocations also 
elsewhere in the Sava River basin during the night, but did not 
respond. 
  The Bosnian Serb army command in Herzegovina reported 
reduced 
Moslem operations and only sporadic fire from small-arms and 
anti-aircraft guns from the direction of Gorazde in the east. 
  In the coming days, Moslems are likely to launch assaults on 
Cajnice, Ustikolina and Kalinovik in the southeast and Borci in 
central Bosnia, the source said and attributed the present 
comparative lull in the fighting to the Bairam festival. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

