<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic Tells Muslims `Struggle Not Over' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1303101694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0909 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1303101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sarajevo mosques were full of believers this 
morning; the Beg's Mosque in particular where the Muslims were 
addressed by the head of the Islamic community in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Reis Ulema Mustafa Ceric. [passage omitted] 
  The believers were also addressed by the President of the 
Presidency of ours state, Alija Izetbegovic. Here is an excerpt 
from his address: 
  [Begin Izetbegovic recording] On this occasion we should 
remember those who are facing considerable difficulties even 
today: those in Maglaj, Bihac, or near Olovo. Thank God, it is 
somewhat easier in some other places, Allah Akbar. This is a 
chance to remember them and to ask the God to help them, to give 
patience to the weak and power to the strong to endure. This is 
perhaps a chance to remember with pride that we belong to a 
huge, huge mass of people, celebrating Bairam today--a billion 
people-- and, like us, hundreds of millions are attending Bairam 
prayers, marking this great day. 
  You must know that the struggle is not over yet. More 
difficult days are ahead. However, do not be afraid, we belong 
to a nation which believes that you die once and live twice. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

