<H3> <TI>   Head of SRI Counterespionage Deposed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1403113194 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI in Romanian 12 Mar 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU1403113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Dan Maracineanu: "Major General Gheorghe </F>
Diaconescu, the Head of the Counterespionage Division of the 
SRI, Has Been Deposed and Is Being Investigated by a Special 
Commission"] 
  [Text] On Monday, 7 March 1994, Major General Gheorghe 
Diaconescu, chief of the Counterespionage Division of the 
Romanian Intelligence Service [SRI], was removed from office. 
Virgil Magureanu, director of SRI, has ordered a full 
investigation of the activity of Major General Gheorghe 
Diaconescu. 
  Sources from the SRI leadership have told us that the cause 
that led to the demotion of the counterespionage division head 
is "a complicated one." 
  Despite the fact that one of the rumors that are circulating 
claimed that Major General Diaconescu had been placed under 
arrest, our own investigations have proved that this was a false 
report. 

</TEXT>

