<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PD Head: Early Election Would Lead to Disaster </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1203184494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1203184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting of the Democratic Party [PD] Steering 
Collegium, Chairman Petre Roman outlined the party's position 
regarding the current political issues. 
  In his speech, Roman said that the only way to solve the 
current crisis situation is to conclude a national pact among 
the PD, the Democratic Convention of Romania [CDR], and the 
Social Democracy Party of Romania [PDSR]. 
  The PD chairman also briefed the meeting's attendants about 
the PD's [separate] negotiations that are currently under way 
with the CDR and the PDSR and presented the party's stance 
regarding the [6 March] government reshuffle and the possibility 
of early elections. Referring to the latter issue, Roman said 
that in the PD's view, early elections would lead to a disaster, 
since the electorate, which was betrayed during the last 
electoral campaign, has lost confidence in everyone and 
everything. 

</TEXT>

