<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minimum Monthly Gross Salary Set at 60,000 Lei </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1203184394 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
0500 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1203184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] At its weekly meeting yesterday, the government 
adopted a decision on the altering of the nationwide minimum 
monthly gross salary, the payment of which is guaranteed by the 
government, setting it at 60,000 lei for 178 worked hours [per 
month]. 
  Among the draft bills that were examined and adopted 
yesterday, we would like to mention the one referring to 
Romania's adherence to the General Accord on the Immunities and 
Privileges of the Council of Europe and the one proposing that 
parliament ratify the European Convention on the Prevention of 
Torture and Inhuman or Degrading Punishment or Handling of 
Persons. The aforementioned documents are intended to make 
Romania adjust to the institutional standards of the Council of 
Europe, a communique released by the government says. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

