<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agree to 2 Cantons </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1303154194 Paris AFP in English 1527 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1303154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, March 13 (AFP)--Bosnian Croats and Moslems 
reached an agreement here Sunday [13 March] on creating a canton 
for each group in central Bosnia, authoritative Croat sources 
announced. 
  The accord came after talks on forming a Croat-Moslem 
federation in Bosnia-Herzegovina resumed at the U.S. Embassy, 
amid signs that negotiators would probably reach an overall 
agreement later in the day. 
  Croatian Foreign Minister Mate Granic earlier said: "We 
shall 
try to finish up this morning," while Bosnian Prime Minister 
Haris Silajdzic said he was "still optimistic." 
  Croat sources said late Saturday [12 March] only "a few 
technical problems" remained and a global accord would probably 
be announced Sunday. 
  The behind-closed-doors talks began here on March 4 after 
Granic and Silajdzic signed an initial agreement on March 1 in 
Washington. 

</TEXT>

