<H3> <TI>   Khan Kubrat Anchors Near Vidin; Crew Detained </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1303183194 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1303183194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Bulgarian vessel Khan Kubrat has anchored at 
the 793-km point near Vidin with empty tanks. There were 21 
people on board--the crew and a woman, and they have all been 
detained at the regional Internal Affairs Ministry Directorate. 
The captain of the vessel is Konstantin Stoyanov, 49, from Ruse. 
  REUTER disseminated a photograph accompanied by a text that 
recalls the history of the vessel's strange trip. This means 
that tomorrow Bulgaria's name will be on the front page of every 
major newspapers in the world. The UN Security Council will 
also discuss the incident. 
  Meanwhile, the State River Sailing Inspectorate in Vidin has 
refused to issue a statement for the radio. It was pointed out 
from the Vidin Inspectorate that they are subordinate to the Lom 
Inspectorate, and the chairman of the Lom Inspectorate will have 
a statement for the public tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

