<F P=102>  AU1103205794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1103205794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A statement issued by the Foreign Minister 
expresses serious concern regarding the continuing incident with 
the Bulgarian vessel the Khan Kubrat. Despite the initial 
promises of assistance made by the responsible Serbian bodies 
and their assurances that the vessel and its cargo were under 
control, the fuel cargo is being discharged from the Khan Kubrat 
barge train. 
  The Foreign Ministry insists that the unloading operation 
should be stopped immediately and the ship returned to Bulgaria 
together with its cargo and crew. 
  The commander of a military patrol launch belonging to the 
Western European Union has reported to the State Navigation 
Inspectorate in Vidin that at about 2200 hours [2000 GMT] this 
evening the Khan Kubrat vessel is expected to arrive in the port 
of Vidin together with its crew. The monitoring bodies have 
made arrangements for the reception of the vessel. 

