<H3> <TI>   Dimitrov Receives Delegation of FRY Bulgarians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1403163694 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1400 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1403163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 14 March Mr. Filip Dimitrov received a delegation 
of the Democratic Union of Bulgarians in Yugoslavia led by Ivan 
Grigorov, chairman of the Union. 
  During the meeting, which was attended by Asparukh Panov, 
deputy chairman of the Union of Democratic Forces [SDS] on 
foreign policy issues, the guests imparted information related 
to the crude violation of the rights of the Bulgarian minority 
in the spheres of religion, education, use of their native 
tongue, and preserving cultural and historical heritage. Alarm 
was expressed over the attempts to ban the Democratic Union of 
Bulgarians in Yugoslavia, officially forcing the Bulgarians to 
adopt Serbian names and disseminating the thesis of the 
existence of a Serbian-Shop [Bulgarian Sofia region peasant] 
nation. 
  The possibilities of rendering practical help on the part of 
the SDS in the sphere of training pupils, students, and graduate 
students were discussed. The SDS committed itself to defending 
the rights of the Bulgarians in Yugoslavia in accordance with 
the international documents. 
  The Democratic Union of the Bulgarian in Yugoslavia invited 
an official SDS delegation to visit the regions of Bosilegrad 
and Tsaribrod in the near future. 

</TEXT>

