<H3> <TI>   Luxembourg's Poos Arrives To Discuss Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1303184794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1303184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the invitation of Foreign Minister Stanislav 
Daskalov, Jacques Poos, deputy prime minister and minister of 
foreign affairs of the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg, arrived in 
Bulgaria today. This is how he summarized his intentions for 
tomorrow's talks at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the Council 
of Ministers, and the National Assembly: 
  [Begin Poos recording, in French fading into Bulgarian 
translation] This is a working visit related to our bilateral 
relations. However, I have also come to Bulgaria in my capacity 
as acting chairman of the Western European Union. We will also 
discuss issues of European security. In response to our 
question whether the issue of violating the embargo along the 
Danube River will be discussed, Mr. Poos said that this is not 
the basic goal of his visit, but the issue will be discussed 
anyway. Nevertheless, we do not consider Bulgaria responsible 
for the recent incidents, he stressed. 
  The guest said that at the last meeting of the Western 
European Union in Luxembourg on the ministerial level, it was 
decided to grant Bulgaria an enhanced status, which will 
practically make it an associated member of the Western European 
Union. 
  Mr. Poos will also be received by President Zhelyu Zhelev 
tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

